The index is chosen uniformly at random from `List.length xs`. -/
noncomputable def uniformSelectList (xs : List α) : SProbComp α :=
  SProbComp.mk (λ i : Fin (List.length xs) ↦ xs.get i) (λ i hi ↦ 1 / ↑(List.length xs))

/- Choose a random element from a finset, with equal probability for each element.
The element is chosen uniformly at random from `Finset.mem s`. -/
noncomputable def uniformSelectFinset (s : Finset α) : SProbComp α :=
  SProbComp.mk (λ i : Fin s.card ↦ s.get i) (λ i hi ↦ 1 / ↑s.card)

/- Choose a random element from the type `β` itself, not from a collection.
This is a generalization of `select` in probability theory, where the outcome space is the type itself.
This is noncomputable as we don't have a canonical way to define this for arbitrary types.
We require `Inhabited α` to ensure the existence of an outcome.
The definition is abstract and must be provided by the user. -/
noncomputable def uniformSelect (α : Type) [Inhabited α] : SProbComp α := sorry

/- Choose a random element from the type `β` itself, not from a collection.
This is similar to `uniformSelect` but with an explicit computation.
This is noncomputable as we don't have a canonical way to define this for arbitrary types.
We require `Inhabited α` to ensure the existence of an outcome.
The definition is abstract and must be provided by the user. -/
noncomputable def uniformSelect' (α : Type) [Inhabited α] : SProbComp α := sorry

/- A `SampleableType β` instance means that `β` is a finite inhabited type,
with a computation `selectElem` that selects uniformly at random from the type.
This generally requires choosing some " canonical" ordering for the type,
so we include this to get a computable version of selection.
We also require that each element has the same probability of being chosen from by `selectElem`,
see `SampleableType.probOutput_selectElem` for the reduction when `α` has a `Fintype` instance.
NOTE: universe polymorphism of `β` is hard. -/
class SampleableType (β : Type) where
  selectElem : SProbComp β
  mem_support_selectElem (x : β) : x ∈ support selectElem
